<p>
  If large <b>numbers are printed in blocks</b>, no blanks are set within the numeric keypad, e.&#x202f;g. <codeph>1000000</codeph> (this means that the system deviates from the original).
</p>

<p>
  For <b>percentage specifications</b>: Number spaces %-character; e.&#x202f;g. <codeph>50 %</codeph>.
</p>

<p>
  For <b>temperature specifications</b>, there is a space before the unit; e.&#x202f;g. <codeph>360 Â°C</codeph>.
</p>

